Police on Wednesday were forced to fire in the air several times to disperse Technical University of Mombasa students who were protesting insecurity in the region. Thousands of TUM students who were protesting from Makupa Police station to Kisauni area met resistance at Zam Zam area, where local youth pelted them with stones. During the chaos, police officers were forced to shoot in the air several times to disperse the youth. Several students were injured in the chaos. More to follow...